headline: 5 Top Stocks to Buy in March
summary: 2025 has gotten off to a choppy start as some of the most valuable U.S.-based companies are dragging down the major stock market indexes.  Here's why four Motley Fool contributors think chip giants Nvidia (NASDAQ: NVDA) and Micron Technologies (NASDAQ: MU), travel services company Airbnb (NASDAQ: ABNB), biotech behemoth Vertex Pharmaceuticals (NASDAQ: VRTX), and high-yield dividend stock Enterprise Products Partners (NYSE: EPD) are worth buying in March.  Daniel Foelber (Nvidia): Despite blow-out results and upbeat guidance, Nvidia's stock price fell 8.5% last Thursday after reporting fourth-quarter and full-year fiscal 2025 results.
